description: The FAS Chat, or ‘Faculty and Student/Staff’ Chat Series, is designed to promote a conversation between students and faculty/staff, so that faculty and staff may learn about the many Multi-Cultural Council (MCC) groups and friend organizations at Behrend from the students themselves. Student panelists will discuss the reasons for their group’s formation, the obstacles they face and challenges they have overcome, and will take questions from the audience. This is Behrend Benefiting THON's annual 24 hour no sitting, no sleeping dance marathon! All funds raised will go to benefit THON's sole benefactor, the Four Diamonds fund which provides emotional support and medical treatment at Penn State Hershey Children's hospital. Students from 30+ campus clubs and organizations come together for one cause; enhancing the lives of children and families impacted by childhood cancer. Each of the 24 hour dance is filled with fun interactive activities provided by an on campus club or organization. These clubs provide energy and excitement to the dancers and morales whom are committed to standing awake for 20+ hours for the children who can’t. The event, not only for the Behrend community but the families that we support. 24FAC is supported by businesses who help support the cause by donating towards the event. Help us continue to grow on our mission to provide emotional and financial support, spread awareness, and ensure funding for critical research ― all in pursuit of a cure.  Hosted by: Behrend Benefiting THON  Additional Information can be found at: https://behrend.campuslabs.com/engage/event/7618861
